apertium-separable
------------------------------------------
Lttoolbox provides a module for reordering separable/discontiguous multiwords
and processing them in the pipeline. Multiwords are manually written in an
additional xml-format dictionary.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.3-1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libicu70-70.1-1
  liblttoolbox3-3.7.1-1bl1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.3-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.39-1
  cygport-0.35.5-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  libicu-devel-70.1-1
  liblttoolbox-devel-3.7.1-1bl1
  libxml2-devel-2.9.12-2
  make-4.4-1
  utf8cpp-3.2.1-1bl1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-separable

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/apertium/apertium-separable/archive/refs/tags/v0.6.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack apertium-separable-0.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./apertium-separable-0.6.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/apertium-separable-0.6.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/apertium-separable-0.6.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(apertium-separable)
  /usr/bin/lsx-proc.exe
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/apertium-separable.pc
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/apertium-separable.README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/README
  /usr/share/doc/apertium-separable/readme.md

